news.title: Germany: PBB's profit plunges 74% in Q2 2024
news.para: PBB in recent years bet heavily on the U.S. market by offering commercial real estate loans, which across the industry have succumbed to pressure from high office vacancies and falling property prices following rises in interest rates and a trend towards home-working since the pandemic.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body to attach bank accounts of property tax defaulters
news.para: The Bruhat Bengaluru Mahanagara Palike (BBMP) has gained new powers to recover property tax arrears by attaching the bank accounts of defaulters. With around three lakh properties on the tax default list, BBMP issued a notification allowing them to serve attachment warrants to banks and take action under Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita-2023 if banks fail to comply.

news.title: Navi Mumbai builder loses more than Rs 13.5 crore in share trading fraud
news.para: Based on a complaint, a case under sections 319(2) (cheating by personation) and 318(4) (cheating) of the Bharatiya Nyay Sanhita and relevant provisions of the Information Technology Act was registered at Cyber police station, senior inspector Gajanan Kadam of the Cyber police station said.

news.title: Sunteck Lifestyles settles legal disputes with Grand Valley General Trading LLC
news.para: Sunteck Lifestyles & Grand Valley General Trading LLC had formed GGICO Sunteck, a joint venture company, to develop a real estate project in Dubai. There is no compensation/ penalty to be paid as part of the settlement process.

news.title: ArisInfra Solutions files draft IPO papers with SEBI to raise Rs 600 crore
news.para: The Mumbai-based company plans to mop-up about Rs 120 crore through a pre-IPO placement. If such placement is undertaken, the amount raised will be deducted from the total IPO size.

news.title: Gurugram: ED restitutes 78 flats to buyers of SRS Group's Pearl, City & Prime projects
news.para: The process to restitute 78 flats of genuine homebuyers in these SRS projects has been initiated following the Appellate Tribunal, instituted under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA), issuing an order on August 12 allowing the ED to return these flats worth a total Rs 20.15 crore to their rightful claimants.

news.title: Three entities settle insider trading charges with Sebi in PNB Housing Finance case
news.para: ​Those who settled the case are -- Sidhant Chandalia, Naysar Parikh and Ronak Narendra Parikh, according to two separate orders passed by the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi).

news.title: Ansal Housing posts net profit of Rs 41.59 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Ansal Housing's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 125.48 crore in Q1 FY25, a growth of 59.16 per cent from Rs 78.84 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: UK's Bellway cancels takeover proposal for Crest Nicholson
news.para: Shares in Bellway rose about 4% following the news on Tuesday, while Crest stock, which had gained 15% since the approach was disclosed in June, dropped about 9%.

news.title: Omaxe posts net loss of Rs 146.98 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Omaxe's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 385.23 crore in Q1 FY25, a growth of 74.43 per cent from Rs 220.85 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Ashiana Housing & Arihant Foundations to invest Rs 225 crore on a residential project in Chennai
news.para: The companies will invest approximately Rs 225 crore in the project and sales realization is estimated to be Rs 450 crore.

news.title: Puducherry CM hikes subsidy given to Kamaraj Housing scheme beneficiaries
news.para: ​​In all, each beneficiary would get Rs 10 lakh. The purpose of granting the subsidy is to replace huts with concrete structures. The scheme is named after former chief minister of Tamil Nadu K Kamaraj.

news.title: NBCC (India)'s net profit up 38.47% in Q1 FY25
news.para: NBCC (India)'s net consolidated total income stood at Rs 2,197.83 crore in Q1 FY25, a growth of 11.34 per cent from Rs 1,974.03 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Awfis Space Solutions posts net profit of Rs 2.78 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: As of June 30, 2024, Awfis Space Solutions has surpassed 100,000 operational seats and 169 operational centers. In Q1 FY25, it witnessed net addition of 5,368 seats and nine centers.

news.title: BigBloc Construction's net profit dips 48.64% in Q1 FY25
news.para: BigBloc Construction's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 52.26 crore in Q1 FY25, a dip of 4.86 per cent from Rs 54.93 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Interarch Building Products' Rs 600-crore IPO to open on August 19
news.para: The IPO is a combination of a fresh issue of shares worth up to Rs 200 crore and an offer-for-sale of up to 44.47 lakh shares valued at Rs 400 crore, at the upper end of the price band, by the promoters and investor-selling shareholders. This aggregates the total issue size to Rs 600 crore.

news.title: Kotak Investment Advisor to invest Rs 450 crore in Supertech’s stuck project in Noida
news.para: Noida authority, which has to recover dues of Rs 3,319 crore from the project, has asked KIAL to deposit Rs 50 crore with the authority and an agreement will be done between Supertech, KIAL and Noida authority to open an escrow account.

news.title: Delhi civic body will put Bhalswa Dairy colony's demolition drive on hold till August 16
news.para: In July, the court had directed the authorities to ensure that unauthorised construction in all dairy colonies in the national capital is removed and asked them to take immediate steps for shifting dairies from Bhalswa to Ghogha dairy colony within four weeks.

news.title: Blackstone sells 3,000 homes to Britain's Universities Superannuation Scheme
news.para: Blackstone sold the portfolio to academia pension fund, the Universities Superannuation Scheme (USS), which manages more than 75 billion pounds ($96 billion) of assets, in a deal worth 405 million pounds ($519 million).

news.title: JV Ventures and Terminus Group form $200 million hospitality platform
news.para: The venture, with equal investment from both firms, will focus on developing and managing mid-market branded luxury hotels in cities like Thiruvananthapuram, Visakhapatnam, Tirupati, and Hyderabad. Over the next five years, the platform aims to develop 25 assets with over 3,000 keys. The initiative is part of a broader trend in India's growing hospitality sector, driven by increased travel and new investor interest.
